byline.original: By FRANK L. KLUCKHOHN Special to THE NEW YORK TIMES

abstract: Maj K Roosevelt reptd en route to Norway; Germans seize U S mil supplies in Bergen intended for Sweden and Finland; State Dept denies representations were made in Berlin to prevent seizure of 400 trucks for Finland
snippet: WASHINGTON, April 30--Sizable stocks of American military supplies on their way to Sweden and Finland are now in the hands of German invaders in Norway and may be in use against the AngloFrench expeditionary force and the Norwegians....

headline.main: Nazis Seize U.S. Arms in Norway Intended for the Swedes and Finns; 500 Sub-Machine Guns, Millions of Bullets, 400 Trucks and Some Planes Taken-- State Department Is Silent

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, April 30--Sizable stocks of American military supplies on their way to Sweden and Finland are now in the hands of German invaders in Norway and may be in use against the AngloFrench expeditionary force and the Norwegians.
